{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying annotation implementation**\\n\\nIŌĆÖm considering that implementing an annotation interface in a local class isnŌĆÖt exactly an annotation itself. ItŌĆÖs more of an instance of the annotation type rather than a Proxy. I think its methods direct Method.invoke, which might be used by BB. Also, it seems like reflection isnŌĆÖt necessary here. However, since the Annotation interface needs an annotationType, it could still be implemented. Let's explore this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering precedence and implementation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the precedence of operators, like how ^ is lower than +. It seems I need to use parentheses for clarity. I could also use this in an assert statement if I wanted to. Maybe I can avoid using equals or hash in the implementation? ItŌĆÖs true that the interface inherits from Object, so it shouldnŌĆÖt require an override. I'm just mulling over the best way to handle this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eCLPuaw75WknTHrbxYk1hopi|fc_0beecbd0b67be1590169f18bb9e63881969c09f557a623cb99", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 898, "output": 1797, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27783, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777437599038, "responseId": "resp_0beecbd0b67be1590169f18b9fc110819690c8b0a63662b43b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_eCLPuaw75WknTHrbxYk1hopi|fc_0beecbd0b67be1590169f18bb9e63881969c09f557a623cb99", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\": \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"org.modelmapper.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777437